import cv2
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

initial_img_rgb = cv2.imread('img/Nature.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)  
initial_img_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(initial_img_rgb, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
plt.imshow(initial_img_rgb)
plt.title('Initial RGB Image')
plt.show()

colors = ('b', 'g', 'r')

for i, col in enumerate(colors):
    hist_rgb = cv2.calcHist([initial_img_rgb],
                            [i], None,
                            [256],
                            [0, 256])

    plt.plot(hist_rgb, color=col)
    plt.xlim([0, 256])

plt.show()

height, width, _ = initial_img_rgb.shape
for i in range(0, height - 1):
    for j in range(0, width - 1):

        pixel = initial_img_rgb[i, j]
        pixel[0] = 255 - pixel[0]
        pixel[1] = 255 - pixel[1]
        pixel[2] = 255 - pixel[2]

        initial_img_rgb[i, j] = pixel
plt.imshow(initial_img_rgb)
plt.title('Negative Transformed RGB Image')
plt.show()

colors = ('b', 'g', 'r')

for i, col in enumerate(colors):

    hist_transformed_rgb = cv2.calcHist([initial_img_rgb],
                                        [i], None,
                                        [256],
                                        [0, 256])

    plt.plot(hist_transformed_rgb, color=col)
    plt.xlim([0, 256])
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

original_image = cv2.imread('img/Nature.jpg')

original_image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(original_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

epsilon = 1e-8
c_value = 255 / np.log(1 + np.max(original_image_rgb) + epsilon)
log_transformed_image = c_value * (np.log(original_image_rgb + epsilon))

log_transformed_image = np.nan_to_num(log_transformed_image)

log_transformed_image = np.array(log_transformed_image, dtype=np.uint8)

plt.imshow(original_image_rgb)
plt.title('Original RGB Image')
plt.show()

plt.imshow(log_transformed_image)
plt.title('Log Transformed RGB Image')
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

original_image = cv2.imread('img/Nature.jpg')
original_image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(original_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
gamma_value = 2   

gamma_corrected_image = np.power(original_image_rgb / 255.0, gamma_value)
gamma_corrected_image = np.uint8(gamma_corrected_image * 255.0)
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))

axes[0].imshow(original_image_rgb)
axes[0].set_title('Original RGB Image')

axes[1].imshow(gamma_corrected_image)
axes[1].set_title(f'Gamma-Corrected (Gamma = {gamma_value})')

plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

original_image = cv2.imread('img/Nature.jpg')
blue, green, red = cv2.split(original_image)
threshold_value = 128

solarized_blue = np.where(blue < threshold_value, blue, 255 - blue)
solarized_green = np.where(green < threshold_value, green, 255 - green)
solarized_red = np.where(red < threshold_value, red, 255 - red)

solarized_image = cv2.merge((solarized_blue, solarized_green, solarized_red))

plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(original_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title('Original Image')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(solarized_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title('Solarized Image')

plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

original_image = cv2.imread('img/Nature.jpg')
blue, green, red = cv2.split(original_image)

equalized_blue = cv2.equalizeHist(blue)
equalized_green = cv2.equalizeHist(green)
equalized_red = cv2.equalizeHist(red)

equalized_image = cv2.merge((equalized_blue, equalized_green, equalized_red))

plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(original_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title('Original Image')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(equalized_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title('Equalized Image')

plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

image = cv2.imread('img/Nature.jpg')
b, g, r = cv2.split(image)
hist_b = cv2.calcHist([b], [0], None, [256], [0, 256])
hist_g = cv2.calcHist([g], [0], None, [256], [0, 256])
hist_r = cv2.calcHist([r], [0], None, [256], [0, 256])
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(hist_b, color='blue')
plt.title('   B')

plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(hist_g, color='green')
plt.title('   G')

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(hist_r, color='red')
plt.title('   R')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
